00:34:14,520 --> 00:34:18,399
I think you and I could do a lot
more business together, Mr Mullen.

481
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,759
I very much hope so.

482
00:34:19,760 --> 00:34:22,239
We will most definitely be in touch.

483
00:34:22,240 --> 00:34:23,799
Oh, and remember...

484
00:34:23,800 --> 00:34:26,799
TOGETHER: "If you don't ask..."

485
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:27,840
THEY LAUGH

486
00:34:48,040 --> 00:34:51,319
What do you feed
your staff on, Mr Mullen?

487
00:34:51,320 --> 00:34:53,279
I'm sorry?

488
00:34:53,280 --> 00:34:56,719
Buddy, you're either on a hell of
a diet or you have terminal cancer.

489
00:34:56,720 --> 00:34:58,799
Oh. You're right.
He has lost some weight.

490
00:34:58,800 --> 00:34:59,958
Six stone, actually.

491
00:34:59,959 --> 00:35:01,840
- What did you say?
- In as many weeks.

492
00:35:01,841 --> 00:35:06,279
Six stone in six weeks?
How?

493
00:35:06,280 --> 00:35:08,759
- Oh, no, that's private.
- Oh. Don't be like that.

494
00:35:08,760 --> 00:35:11,759
You wouldn't want to make
little Dana cross, would you?

495
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:13,640
Weight loss is our business.

496
00:35:14,760 --> 00:35:16,199
It's a new diet drink.

497
00:35:16,200 --> 00:35:17,239
A diet drink?

498
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:19,239
Yeah.
Just one spoonful, and bingo.

499
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:22,719
What diet drink? Where did
you get it, this diet drink?

500
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:26,399
How come I haven't heard
about this new diet drink?

501
00:35:26,400 --> 00:35:30,479
Tell me, or you'll be losing
a couple more ounces right here.

502
00:35:30,480 --> 00:35:32,599
Cos it's not for sale.

503
00:35:32,600 --> 00:35:35,519
Er, cos it's still being tested.

504
00:35:35,520 --> 00:35:39,040
Cos I sort of... nicked it.

505
00:35:41,960 --> 00:35:46,479
My missus works as a lab
assistant for Spitz-Kleinman.

506
00:35:46,480 --> 00:35:48,639
They're a pharmaceutical company.

507
00:35:48,640 --> 00:35:49,840
We know who they are.

508
00:35:49,841 --> 00:35:53,319
Yeah, and occasionally she'd bring
some of her work home with her.

509
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:56,439
Anyway, she was talking about
this new weight-loss product

510
00:35:56,440 --> 00:36:00,079
they'd been testing on rats,
called, er, Reducio.

511
00:36:00,080 --> 00:36:03,279
It had been a bit of a
disappointment, she said,

512
00:36:03,280 --> 00:36:10,439
so... she bought a few bottles of it
home to do some more work on and...

513
00:36:10,440 --> 00:36:14,719
It's OK, Phillips, we
won't tell anyone. Go on.

514
00:36:14,720 --> 00:36:16,639
Well, I just borrowed a bottle.

515
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:19,079
I've always struggled with me weight

516
00:36:19,080 --> 00:36:22,679
and, well, I wanted to see
if this was the one, you know,

517
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:25,319
the one diet product
that actually worked.

518
00:36:25,320 --> 00:36:27,479
And boy, did it?

519
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:29,359
Yeah, just one spoonful a day.

520
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:31,879
You know, you can still
eat anything you want.

521
00:36:31,880 --> 00:36:33,040
And the fat...

522
00:36:34,560 --> 00:36:36,319
It all comes out in your pores.

523
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:38,799
You sweat it out!

524
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:41,319
Yeah, you sweat all the fat out!

525
00:36:41,320 --> 00:36:43,359
That is genius.

526
00:36:43,360 --> 00:36:47,240
And what did your wife say when
she saw how much you'd lost?

527
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:52,639
Well my wife didn't say anything.

528
00:36:52,640 --> 00:36:54,919
She didn't say anything?
You were a freak!

529
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:58,159
When you stood on the scales,
it just said, "To be continued".

530
00:36:58,160 --> 00:37:00,159
She must have said something!

531
00:37:00,160 --> 00:37:02,280
No. No, no, cos she didn't know.

532
00:37:04,600 --> 00:37:06,560
You see, just before
I took the bottle,

533
00:37:06,561 --> 00:37:09,800
she told me she was leaving me
for a body-builder from Purley.

534
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:13,319
She left that night.

535
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:15,159
DANA GASPS

536
00:37:15,160 --> 00:37:19,479
Oh! Oh! Phillips! Excellent news!

537
00:37:19,480 --> 00:37:21,079
What!?

538
00:37:21,080 --> 00:37:23,919
That you have lost so much
weight is excellent news!

539
00:37:23,920 --> 00:37:25,800
But let me just confirm one thing...

540
00:37:25,801 --> 00:37:30,679
that your wife has absolutely no idea
the product worked so well for you?

541
00:37:30,680 --> 00:37:33,039
No. No, none at all.
No.

542
00:37:33,040 --> 00:37:37,799
Do you know when Spitz-Kleinman were
planning on starting human trials?

543
00:37:37,800 --> 00:37:41,599
Well, er, it could be a
matter of months, she said.

544
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:43,519
Or even a year.

545
00:37:43,520 --> 00:37:48,759
Do you, I mean to say, that is...

546
00:37:48,760 --> 00:37:52,959
Do you think we could have
an incy-wincy little look

547
00:37:52,960 --> 00:37:57,080
at this bottle?
Maurice?

548
00:37:58,200 --> 00:38:02,239
Oh, I mean, I'd love to.

549
00:38:02,240 --> 00:38:03,799
Dana.

550
00:38:03,800 --> 00:38:06,200
HE INHALES DEEPLY

551
00:38:07,200 --> 00:38:10,240
But I finished the last of it
two days ago, I'm afraid.

552
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:15,559
OK, no problem.

553
00:38:15,560 --> 00:38:19,599
Well, why don't we
pop into the kitchen

554
00:38:19,600 --> 00:38:23,559
and get you some lard
or refined sugars

555
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:28,239
or whatever it is you
generally like to eat,

556
00:38:28,240 --> 00:38:31,120
while we have a nice little
chat with Mr Mullen?

557
00:38:35,680 --> 00:38:39,599
Do you have any idea how much
a product like that could be worth?

558
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:42,519
One that actually does
what we say it does?

559
00:38:42,520 --> 00:38:44,799
We could make billions!
Literally billions!

560
00:38:44,800 --> 00:38:46,760
We sell it as a health
supplement, "aiding

561
00:38:46,761 --> 00:38:48,719
weight loss", to
bypass the regs.

562
00:38:48,720 --> 00:38:50,439
And beat Spitz to the market!

563
00:38:50,440 --> 00:38:53,719
No more looking over our shoulders,
no more fighting off lawsuits.

564
00:38:53,720 --> 00:38:56,639
Instead, we'd be feted,
we'd be honoured!

565
00:38:56,640 --> 00:38:59,439
The Nobel Prize for services to fat!

566
00:38:59,440 --> 00:39:02,639
Arise, Sir Dean and Dana!

567
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:03,679
Of Deville!

568
00:39:03,680 --> 00:39:04,719
THEY GASP

569
00:39:04,720 --> 00:39:06,639
Excuse me.

570
00:39:06,640 --> 00:39:10,800
Sorry to interrupt, but aren't
you forgetting something?

571
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:14,239
He used it all, remember?

572
00:39:14,240 --> 00:39:16,999
You don't actually have the drug.

573
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:19,639
What do have is a man who
successfully broke into

574
00:39:19,640 --> 00:39:22,559
one of the most secure
galleries in London.

575
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:26,159
How much harder can it be
to break in to a laboratory?

576
00:39:26,160 --> 00:39:27,919
- And steal the formula?
- Why not?

577
00:39:27,920 --> 00:39:29,239
HE LAUGHS

578
00:39:29,240 --> 00:39:30,279
Oh, no.

579
00:39:30,280 --> 00:39:32,239
Equal share, the three of us.

580
00:39:32,240 --> 00:39:34,439
This is big pharma, you're talking
about. Those guys are scary.

581
00:39:34,440 --> 00:39:36,159
We pay you a flat fee, then.

582
00:39:36,160 --> 00:39:39,399
You just help us steal it, don't
get involved in any of the rest.

583
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:40,799
Sorry.

584
00:39:40,800 --> 00:39:42,999
- Same as for the egg.
- Not interested.

585
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:45,559
- 100, then. - Nope.
- OK, double.

586
00:39:45,560 --> 00:39:49,039
200,000 sterling. COD.

587
00:39:49,040 --> 00:39:50,520
Then you're out.

588
00:39:54,640 --> 00:39:56,719
A quarter of a million,

589
00:39:56,720 --> 00:39:58,560
and I'll do it.

590
00:40:00,360 --> 00:40:02,360
Quarter of a million it is.

591
00:40:03,520 --> 00:40:06,679
But this time, he'll
come along for the ride.

592
00:40:06,680 --> 00:40:07,959
What?!

593
00:40:07,960 --> 00:40:10,439
You want Dean to take
part in the break-in?

594
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:13,559
Just as an observer.
I want to be absolutely certain

595
00:40:13,560 --> 00:40:17,319
that we're handing over a quarter
of a brick for the real deal.

596
00:40:17,320 --> 00:40:20,240
- Er, sweetheart, can...
- Be quiet, Dean. OK!

597
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:24,359
It's your money.

598
00:40:24,360 --> 00:40:27,200
But as an observer,
nothing more.

599
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:33,479
That's a kayaking course.

600
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:36,319
That one's rock climbing
up one of them walls.

601
00:40:36,320 --> 00:40:39,319
Oh, and that's a
ballroom dancing course.

602
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:41,919
"The Merengue, the Salsa,
the American Smooth."

603
00:40:41,920 --> 00:40:44,759
Blimey, just reading about
them's making me hungry.

604
00:40:44,760 --> 00:40:46,279
But that's the thing, isn't it?

605
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:49,839
Nothing wrong with having a blow-out,
if you're burning off the calories.

606
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:51,200
Yeah.
I know, I know, I know.

607
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:55,799
What? Why would you not even try it?
Just one of 'em, surely.

608
00:40:55,800 --> 00:41:00,159
- And why wouldn't you?
- I dunno. It's just...

609
00:41:00,160 --> 00:41:01,320
What?

610
00:41:02,360 --> 00:41:05,119
Oh, it's, going on
your own, isn't it?

611
00:41:05,120 --> 00:41:06,278
It's the same for me.

612
00:41:06,279 --> 00:41:08,720
If I had someone to go
with, I'd do it in a shot.

613
00:41:08,721 --> 00:41:11,720
- Would you, really?
- Like a shot.

614
00:41:13,040 --> 00:41:14,659
So don't you know
anyone, then, that we

615
00:41:14,660 --> 00:41:16,259
can ring and ask, you
know, to take you?

616
00:41:16,760 --> 00:41:18,479
Yeah, I do know this one fella.

617
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:22,159
He's a bit of a numpty, but
I just think he's painfully shy.

618
00:41:22,160 --> 00:41:23,240
But I really like him

619
00:41:23,241 --> 00:41:26,679
and I'd love to spend some more time
with him when I get out of here.

620
00:41:26,680 --> 00:41:28,079
Oh. OK, yeah.

621
00:41:28,080 --> 00:41:30,320
Pass us a phone,
I'll give him a bell.

622
00:41:32,920 --> 00:41:34,560
Yeah, all right, there you go.

623
00:41:39,880 --> 00:41:41,639
It's ringing.

624
00:41:41,640 --> 00:41:43,440
Mine's ringing now.

625
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:47,319
Hello?

626
00:41:47,320 --> 00:41:49,639
- Hi, is this Eddie?
- Yeah, speaking.

627
00:41:49,640 --> 00:41:53,119
Hi, Eddie, it's Carol.
I'd like to know, when I get out,

628
00:41:53,120 --> 00:41:55,200
will you go ballroom dancing with me?

629
00:41:59,360 --> 00:42:00,840
Hello?
Anybody here?

630
00:42:06,360 --> 00:42:07,720
Service!

631
00:42:09,120 --> 00:42:11,519
Cor, disgraceful behaviour, innit?

632
00:42:11,520 --> 00:42:13,920
Just can't get the staff these days.

633
00:42:16,160 --> 00:42:17,519
So.

634
00:42:17,520 --> 00:42:21,879
All we have to do,
is get in to one of their labs,

635
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:24,360
plant the formula inside it,
and get out of the lab,

636
00:42:24,361 --> 00:42:27,199
so that we can get back in again
to take out what we've just put in.

637
00:42:27,200 --> 00:42:29,879
- Simple!
- Ash, can you handle the data?

638
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:31,679
I've just lost six stone,

639
00:42:31,680 --> 00:42:34,759
I am strong, I am empowered,
I am beautiful.

640
00:42:34,760 --> 00:42:36,120
- Is that a yes?
- Go on, then.

641
00:42:36,121 --> 00:42:38,359
Sean, we'll need
some promotional stuff.

642
00:42:38,360 --> 00:42:39,440
Albert, fake IDs?

643
00:42:39,441 --> 00:42:40,639
No problem.

644
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:42,159
Emma, we need you inside.

645
00:42:42,160 --> 00:42:44,919
Now, they're looking for domestics.
Give them a call.

646
00:42:44,920 --> 00:42:47,599
And I need to work out a way
to get us undisturbed access

647
00:42:47,600 --> 00:42:50,240
to a lab for an hour or so.

648
00:42:52,840 --> 00:42:56,839
The key, in jobs like this one,
is to contrive a way

649
00:42:56,840 --> 00:42:59,759
to walk in through the front
door, find the right lab,

650
00:42:59,760 --> 00:43:02,199
take the formula,
and walk out again, calmly,

651
00:43:02,200 --> 00:43:03,999
without attracting attention.

652
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:05,119
Here you are.

653
00:43:05,120 --> 00:43:07,839
And right now, I have a team
of experts working very hard

654
00:43:07,840 --> 00:43:09,040
to make that plan work.

655
00:43:09,041 --> 00:43:11,519
Dean.
You and I will be officers from

656
00:43:11,520 --> 00:43:14,639
the National lnstitute for
Health and Clinical Excellence,

657
00:43:14,640 --> 00:43:17,559
come to do a spot-check
on their clinical facilities.

658
00:43:17,560 --> 00:43:20,999
Once we're inside reception, we will
tell security we need to inspect

659
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:24,919
two labs, that we will need
for no longer than 15 minutes.

660
00:43:24,920 --> 00:43:27,599
We'll also tell them we
need those labs cleared.

661
00:43:27,600 --> 00:43:31,519
Dean, you and I will have IDs and
numbers to call for verification,

662
00:43:31,520 --> 00:43:35,039
though any call they make
will be diverted to one of my team.

663
00:43:35,040 --> 00:43:37,319
You've done this before.

664
00:43:37,320 --> 00:43:38,559
HE SMIRKS

665
00:43:38,560 --> 00:43:42,119
All we need to do now is find out which
lab Reducio is being developed in.

666
00:43:42,120 --> 00:43:44,799
My IT experts are hacking
their mainframe to find out...

667
00:43:44,800 --> 00:43:47,999
so that we know which lab
we want to "randomly" check.

668
00:43:48,000 --> 00:43:51,120
Once we have that information,
we're good to go.

669
00:44:03,840 --> 00:44:06,240
- Healthy lifestyle, healthy fridge.
- Oh, Eddie.

670
00:44:08,320 --> 00:44:10,559
Thank you so much.

671
00:44:10,560 --> 00:44:12,280
You're such a lovely man.

672
00:44:31,920 --> 00:44:34,600
Better than a kick in the teeth...

673
00:44:44,160 --> 00:44:45,439
Sean Kennedy?

674
00:44:45,440 --> 00:44:46,559
Yeah?

675
00:44:46,560 --> 00:44:47,919
DS Rivet, Hoxton nick.

676
00:44:47,920 --> 00:44:50,400
I think we need to have
a little chat.

677
00:44:52,480 --> 00:44:53,800
Oh, no.

678
00:45:08,920 --> 00:45:11,519
What the hell's happened?

679
00:45:11,520 --> 00:45:14,079
They're questioning Sean
about the Tenguiz break-in.

680
00:45:14,080 --> 00:45:16,079
Seems he dropped something
that IDs him.

681
00:45:16,080 --> 00:45:18,440
- Oh, my God. Is he going to blab?
- No, of course not.

682
00:45:18,441 --> 00:45:20,079
What's the problem, then?

683
00:45:20,080 --> 00:45:21,439
Kid'll be out in ten,

684
00:45:21,440 --> 00:45:24,119
still got time to make
something of himself.

685
00:45:24,120 --> 00:45:27,319
The problem is that the police
are watching us like hawks...

686
00:45:27,320 --> 00:45:30,159
so we're not going to go ahead
with the Spitz job.

687
00:45:30,160 --> 00:45:33,879
Any of us.
It's suicide.

688
00:45:33,880 --> 00:45:36,240
He's right, I'm sorry, it's over.

689
00:45:37,560 --> 00:45:39,079
Wait!

690
00:45:39,080 --> 00:45:40,559
They're not watching us.

691
00:45:40,560 --> 00:45:42,239
They don't even know about us.

692
00:45:42,240 --> 00:45:43,440
And?

693
00:45:48,440 --> 00:45:49,840
Oh, no.

694
00:45:50,920 --> 00:45:53,919
You mean we do it?!

695
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:55,239
The two of us?
The break-in?

696
00:45:55,340 --> 00:45:57,019
Why not?
We could wear earpieces.

697
00:45:57,520 --> 00:46:00,439
Mullen could talk us through it.
What do you say, Mullen?

698
00:46:00,440 --> 00:46:02,799
- I say you're insane.
- Really? How hard can it be?

699
00:46:02,800 --> 00:46:06,679
Honey, it could...
Shut up! Come on, why not?

700
00:46:06,680 --> 00:46:09,079
We didn't learn this
business overnight.

701
00:46:09,080 --> 00:46:12,119
- It takes years of experience.
- You underestimate me.

702
00:46:12,120 --> 00:46:15,799
You have no idea of some of the
things I've done to make money.

703
00:46:15,800 --> 00:46:19,199
We've never been beaten,
never failed.

704
00:46:19,200 --> 00:46:22,879
Well, you have now.
It's a crazy idea.

705
00:46:22,880 --> 00:46:25,519
Fine. Walk away from
250,000 sterling then.

706
00:46:25,520 --> 00:46:27,919
When we're so close.

707
00:46:27,920 --> 00:46:30,559
So close!

708
00:46:30,560 --> 00:46:33,479
Come on, Mullen!
We can make this work.

709
00:46:33,480 --> 00:46:36,960
Remember how good that
money felt in your hands.

710
00:46:43,560 --> 00:46:45,279
OK.

711
00:46:45,280 --> 00:46:48,720
OK, but we have to move fast, while
they're preoccupied with Sean.

712
00:46:53,040 --> 00:46:54,800
HE CLICKS HIS TEETH

713
00:46:56,200 --> 00:47:00,239
OK, I confess, I can't take it
any longer, I did it.

714
00:47:00,240 --> 00:47:02,039
But of course you did it.

715
00:47:02,040 --> 00:47:04,319
We all know you did it.

716
00:47:04,320 --> 00:47:06,679
Yeah, I did it.

717
00:47:06,680 --> 00:47:09,159
I went to the Tenguiz gallery

718
00:47:09,160 --> 00:47:12,040
and I dropped a bit of litter
on the floor.

719
00:47:14,400 --> 00:47:18,399
I wonder if you'll find it
so funny standing in the dock,

720
00:47:18,400 --> 00:47:20,360
facing down a ten stretch.

721
00:47:23,240 --> 00:47:24,640
Testing, testing.

722
00:47:26,480 --> 00:47:29,439
Cor-blimey guv'nor, it's a real
pea-souper, make no mistake.

723
00:47:29,440 --> 00:47:32,839
Remind me why we thought
this was a good idea.

724
00:47:32,840 --> 00:47:35,039
Dean, they do have
American employees.

725
00:47:35,040 --> 00:47:38,799
Cuppa Rosy-Lee, don't mind
if I do! Ta very much!

726
00:47:38,800 --> 00:47:41,559
I bet Sean's more relaxed
than me right now.

727
00:47:41,560 --> 00:47:46,080
Maybe this time, this time,
we may have gone too far.

728
00:47:48,400 --> 00:47:49,640
Don't say a freakin' word

