at random, numbers three and 14.

734
00:48:05,640 --> 00:48:09,199
'To inspect, we'll need uninterrupted
access for approximately 15 minutes.

735
00:48:09,200 --> 00:48:11,040
'You will wish to confirm our IDs.'

736
00:48:11,041 --> 00:48:14,199
You can talk to our authentication
department on this number.

737
00:48:14,200 --> 00:48:15,680
Thank you so much.

738
00:48:17,520 --> 00:48:21,880
MOBILE RINGS

739
00:48:24,720 --> 00:48:25,839
Good morning,

740
00:48:25,840 --> 00:48:28,740
National lnstitute for Health
and Clinical Excellence

741
00:48:28,741 --> 00:48:31,640
Authentication department.
How can I help you?

742
00:48:35,720 --> 00:48:40,120
'Emma? They're clearing everyone out
of the lab. Put the files in place.'

743
00:49:08,120 --> 00:49:12,239
We had a scientist up in Scotland last
year who caught a new flesh-eating bug.

744
00:49:12,240 --> 00:49:13,700
By the time they got to
him, all that was left

745
00:49:13,701 --> 00:49:16,160
was one thumb and an earlobe.
True story!

746
00:49:35,600 --> 00:49:37,560
Not too obvious, Em.

747
00:49:44,520 --> 00:49:46,160
We're good from here, thank you.

748
00:49:49,840 --> 00:49:51,040
Mullen, we're in.

749
00:49:51,041 --> 00:49:53,200
'OK, now what have you got?

750
00:49:53,201 --> 00:49:55,359
' Three computers, I'm on the first.
Opening it up.

751
00:49:55,360 --> 00:49:57,999
'OK, I can't see anything,

752
00:49:58,000 --> 00:50:00,799
'I can't see anything.'

753
00:50:00,800 --> 00:50:02,599
What am I looking for?
Facts?

754
00:50:02,600 --> 00:50:04,199
Come on, come on, come on.

755
00:50:04,200 --> 00:50:07,120
Are we 100% sure
this is the right lab?

756
00:50:08,200 --> 00:50:09,999
Let me try another computer.

757
00:50:10,000 --> 00:50:12,200
OK, second computer.

758
00:50:13,560 --> 00:50:14,959
- Security?
- Go ahead.

759
00:50:14,960 --> 00:50:17,799
- There's a problem at reception.
- On my way.

760
00:50:17,800 --> 00:50:19,080
Come on, come on!

761
00:50:22,320 --> 00:50:24,239
Hang on.

762
00:50:24,240 --> 00:50:26,199
I got something here, too.

763
00:50:26,200 --> 00:50:29,359
Reducio Optimum 7?

764
00:50:29,360 --> 00:50:31,319
'That's it, that's it.'

765
00:50:31,320 --> 00:50:33,120
It's here, too.

766
00:50:34,200 --> 00:50:36,599
These guys have got
no idea on branding.

767
00:50:36,600 --> 00:50:38,239
It should be Fat-U-Sweat.

768
00:50:38,240 --> 00:50:39,399
'Perspira-Go'.

769
00:50:39,400 --> 00:50:40,919
'Or Fatooze.'

770
00:50:40,920 --> 00:50:43,919
Guys, can we just download
the file and get the hell out?

771
00:50:43,920 --> 00:50:45,240
Now?

772
00:50:51,800 --> 00:50:53,399
Right, what have you got?

773
00:50:53,400 --> 00:50:55,679
Look, this doesn't match.

774
00:50:55,680 --> 00:50:57,240
Security breach.

775
00:51:03,560 --> 00:51:05,080
We've got it!

776
00:51:12,400 --> 00:51:15,999
So near, so very, very near.

777
00:51:16,000 --> 00:51:18,759
This is a very strange sensation.

778
00:51:18,760 --> 00:51:20,719
I'm rooting for the mark.

779
00:51:20,720 --> 00:51:22,319
It's all gone weird.

780
00:51:22,320 --> 00:51:25,280
The Americans
are on the third floor!

781
00:51:26,480 --> 00:51:28,280
(Try the back exit.)

782
00:51:33,880 --> 00:51:36,720
'Boys, the third floor.'

783
00:51:43,720 --> 00:51:46,359
THEY WHOOP AND HOLLER WITH DELIGHT

784
00:51:46,360 --> 00:51:47,400
Come on!

785
00:51:56,520 --> 00:51:58,400
THEY CACKLE GLEEFULLY

786
00:52:01,160 --> 00:52:04,239
'Woo! Woo!

787
00:52:04,240 --> 00:52:05,280
'Go, go, go!'

788
00:52:12,160 --> 00:52:14,679
Your money?

789
00:52:14,680 --> 00:52:16,879
My money.

790
00:52:16,880 --> 00:52:20,239
You... moron!

791
00:52:20,240 --> 00:52:21,560
You didn't seriously think

792
00:52:21,561 --> 00:52:26,039
we were going to give you a quarter
of a million G's, did you?

793
00:52:26,040 --> 00:52:27,599
Why not, we had a deal?

794
00:52:27,600 --> 00:52:29,479
I'll tell you why not.

795
00:52:29,480 --> 00:52:33,119
Because we did all the hard work.
That's why not.

796
00:52:33,120 --> 00:52:34,920
- I think you're being unfair.
- Really?

797
00:52:34,921 --> 00:52:37,279
I did a lot of preparation
behind the scenes.

798
00:52:37,280 --> 00:52:39,160
I did some work you didn't even see.

799
00:52:39,161 --> 00:52:41,919
I don't give a rat's ass what
you did behind the scenes.

800
00:52:41,920 --> 00:52:44,360
We have the formula...
it's being made up

801
00:52:44,361 --> 00:52:46,799
right now... and we don't
need you any more!

802
00:52:46,800 --> 00:52:48,399
Boo-hoo-hoo!

803
00:52:48,400 --> 00:52:50,880
Seriously, what sort of
idiots do you think we are?

804
00:52:50,881 --> 00:52:53,360
The sort who thought I was
attaching a microphone

805
00:52:53,361 --> 00:52:55,839
to that brooch when
actually it was a camera.

806
00:52:55,840 --> 00:53:00,079
A camera that filmed you and your
husband breaking in to Spitz-Kleinman.

807
00:53:00,080 --> 00:53:02,560
Cup of Rosy-Lee, don't mind
if I do, ta very much!

808
00:53:06,760 --> 00:53:09,279
The footage of which
I've put on a DVD

809
00:53:09,280 --> 00:53:11,199
and have given to my assistant

810
00:53:11,200 --> 00:53:14,039
who is at this moment
outside Scotland Yard

811
00:53:14,040 --> 00:53:16,199
waiting for my phone call.

812
00:53:16,200 --> 00:53:18,160
Those sorts of idiots.

813
00:53:19,360 --> 00:53:22,439
250 grand, cash, please.

814
00:53:22,440 --> 00:53:24,679
I almost feel bad.

815
00:53:24,680 --> 00:53:26,800
Yeah, cos they think
that's the worst thing

816
00:53:26,801 --> 00:53:28,919
that's going to happen to them today.

817
00:53:28,920 --> 00:53:31,639
You know,
it almost seems unfair.

818
00:53:31,640 --> 00:53:33,119
Almost!

819
00:53:33,120 --> 00:53:34,559
THEY LAUGH

820
00:53:34,560 --> 00:53:36,520
Are you sure this is
the right formula?

821
00:53:36,521 --> 00:53:39,039
I stole it myself, so I think
I know what I'm doing.

822
00:53:39,040 --> 00:53:41,759
Now shut up and give me the bottle!

823
00:53:41,760 --> 00:53:44,280
- I want to sweat some fat.
- Yeah, me, too! Huh!

824
00:53:55,880 --> 00:53:58,440
You're definitely sweating.

825
00:54:03,360 --> 00:54:04,400
Oh, my...

826
00:54:10,880 --> 00:54:12,799
Yeah, that's what I thought.

827
00:54:12,800 --> 00:54:15,159
Cos that formula's just an emetic.

828
00:54:15,160 --> 00:54:17,520
HE STIFLES VOMITING

829
00:54:18,440 --> 00:54:20,160
A very powerful one, granted.

830
00:54:27,000 --> 00:54:28,399
HE RETCHES VIOLENTLY

831
00:54:28,400 --> 00:54:30,480
But an emetic just the same.

832
00:54:31,480 --> 00:54:32,759
SHE PANTS

833
00:54:32,760 --> 00:54:36,959
We just gave him 250 grand
for something that makes you sick?!

834
00:54:36,960 --> 00:54:39,919
Well, at least we still
have the egg, honey.

835
00:54:39,920 --> 00:54:43,479
HOARSELY: 50 grand for an egg
that's now worth 20 times that.

836
00:54:43,480 --> 00:54:46,719
He may think he had us,
he may think he was smart,

837
00:54:46,720 --> 00:54:49,639
but we're still way up
on the deal!

838
00:54:49,640 --> 00:54:54,319
Who's the idiot now, Mullen?
Who's laughing now!

839
00:54:54,320 --> 00:54:55,680
HE RETCHES

840
00:55:00,680 --> 00:55:01,920
Excuse me?

841
00:55:02,920 --> 00:55:05,480
Is that meant to be in there?

842
00:55:08,600 --> 00:55:11,919
It's believed the egg might have
been accidentally moved by a cleaner

843
00:55:11,920 --> 00:55:13,240
or even a practical joker,

844
00:55:13,241 --> 00:55:15,300
but however it happened,
Lord Tenguiz declared

845
00:55:15,301 --> 00:55:17,359
he was delighted to
have his egg back.

846
00:55:17,360 --> 00:55:19,000
As you can see, the egg is now...

847
00:55:19,001 --> 00:55:22,399
Mmm. I'm no legal expert, but I'd
imagine it's quite difficult

848
00:55:22,400 --> 00:55:26,079
to charge someone for stealing
something that hasn't been stolen.

849
00:55:26,080 --> 00:55:28,040
Wouldn't you say?

850
00:55:34,280 --> 00:55:37,879
'The egg is now back in its rightful
place, and what a piece of art it is.

851
00:55:37,880 --> 00:55:39,080
'It was created... '

852
00:55:39,081 --> 00:55:42,039
But, but, no!

853
00:55:42,040 --> 00:55:47,119
He stole it! He said,
if you used the black light...

854
00:55:47,120 --> 00:55:52,239
If you subject Styteline to a
15-nanosecond blast of black light,

855
00:55:52,240 --> 00:55:54,679
it temporarily changes
the refractive index.

856
00:55:54,680 --> 00:55:58,320
And if you believe that load of old
cobblers, you'll believe anything.

857
00:56:00,400 --> 00:56:02,559
We saw him leave the room with it.

858
00:56:02,560 --> 00:56:04,760
We saw him leave the room with it!

859
00:56:43,680 --> 00:56:45,760
No!

860
00:56:47,360 --> 00:56:50,479
We do the cons!
We're the ones who do the conning!

861
00:56:50,480 --> 00:56:54,520
This really has to be
your best work. The best.

862
00:56:57,720 --> 00:57:02,199
We're the ones who do
the goddamn conning!

863
00:57:02,200 --> 00:57:04,399
So they had to do
the robbery themselves,

864
00:57:04,400 --> 00:57:06,439
or they could have
gone to the police.

865
00:57:06,440 --> 00:57:08,799
Or come after us.
But now, they can't do either.

866
00:57:08,800 --> 00:57:11,959
Yeah, but how would you know
for sure they would offer to do it?

867
00:57:11,960 --> 00:57:14,439
Well, their arrogance,
their greed, their need?

868
00:57:14,440 --> 00:57:17,400
All we had to do was convince them
none of us could do the job.

869
00:57:35,520 --> 00:57:38,719
So you dropped the receipt
deliberately. Unbelievable!

870
00:57:38,720 --> 00:57:40,520
How you lot pull it off,
I've no idea.

871
00:57:40,521 --> 00:57:43,879
Oh! Says the man who pulled off the
greatest con of the 21st century.

872
00:57:43,880 --> 00:57:45,439
It's quite remarkable, Eddie.

873
00:57:45,440 --> 00:57:48,199
You managed to convince Carol
you're an attractive man!

874
00:57:48,200 --> 00:57:50,799
Oi! We think he's a bit
of all right, don't we Carol?

875
00:57:50,800 --> 00:57:53,399
I won't hear a word
against him. Mwah!

876
00:57:53,400 --> 00:57:55,119
OTHERS: Oooh!

877
00:57:55,120 --> 00:57:58,319
All right, how about a toast,
how about a toast?

878
00:57:58,320 --> 00:58:01,799
To Eddie, to Carol, to all of us...
and our good health.

879
00:58:01,800 --> 00:58:03,240
ALL: Our good health!

880
00:58:04,360 --> 00:58:05,999
Hang on.

881
00:58:06,000 --> 00:58:08,799
Crudites, anyone?
Low-fat dip?

882
00:58:08,800 --> 00:58:10,799
He's a friend of
chairman Mao, isn't he?

883
00:58:10,800 --> 00:58:11,919
Ooh!

884
00:58:11,920 --> 00:58:14,519
